# Java testing fundamentals (external cherry-pick)

Source: [jabrena/cursor-rules-java](https://github.com/jabrena/cursor-rules-java) rule 302 — adapted for your monorepo.

## Naming

- `methodUnderTest_stateUnderTest_expectedBehavior`
- Example: `getOrder_whenNotFound_returns404`

## Structure

- Arrange / Act / Assert — blank line between sections.
- One logical behavior per test method.
- Use `@ParameterizedTest` for input variants (null, empty, boundary).

## Assertions

- Prefer AssertJ (`assertThat`) over JUnit legacy asserts.
- Assert exceptions with `assertThatThrownBy` or `assertThrows`.
- No test logic in production code (`if (isTest)` forbidden).

## Agent loop

- Every Copilot/CodeQL fix cites a **named test** in the PR thread reply.
- Test matrix IDs (Phase 1) should map to test method names in close-the-loop Jira comment.
